  48 class Conv(Layer):
  49   """Abstract nD convolution layer (private, used as implementation base).
  50 
  51   This layer creates a convolution kernel that is convolved
  52   (actually cross-correlated) with the layer input to produce a tensor of
  53   outputs. If `use_bias` is True (and a `bias_initializer` is provided),
  54   a bias vector is created and added to the outputs. Finally, if
  55   `activation` is not `None`, it is applied to the outputs as well.
  56 
  57   Arguments:
  58     rank: An integer, the rank of the convolution, e.g. "2" for 2D convolution.
  59     filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space (i.e. the number
  60       of filters in the convolution).
  61     kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of n integers, specifying the
  62       length of the convolution window.
  63     strides: An integer or tuple/list of n integers,
  64       specifying the stride length of the convolution.
  65       Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
  66       any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
  67     padding: One of `"valid"`,  `"same"`, or `"causal"` (case-insensitive).
  68     data_format: A string, one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
  69       The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
  70       `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
  71       `(batch, ..., channels)` while `channels_first` corresponds to
  72       inputs with shape `(batch, channels, ...)`.
  73     dilation_rate: An integer or tuple/list of n integers, specifying
  74       the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
  75       Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
  76       incompatible with specifying any `strides` value != 1.
  77     activation: Activation function. Set it to None to maintain a
  78       linear activation.
  79     use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias.
  80     kernel_initializer: An initializer for the convolution kernel.
  81     bias_initializer: An initializer for the bias vector. If None, the default
  82       initializer will be used.
  83     kernel_regularizer: Optional regularizer for the convolution kernel.
  84     bias_regularizer: Optional regularizer for the bias vector.
  85     activity_regularizer: Optional regularizer function for the output.
  86     kernel_constraint: Optional projection function to be applied to the
  87         kernel after being updated by an `Optimizer` (e.g. used to implement
  88         norm constraints or value constraints for layer weights). The function
  89         must take as input the unprojected variable and must return the
  90         projected variable (which must have the same shape). Constraints are
  91         not safe to use when doing asynchronous distributed training.
  92     bias_constraint: Optional projection function to be applied to the
  93         bias after being updated by an `Optimizer`.
  94     trainable: Boolean, if `True` also add variables to the graph collection
  95       `GraphKeys.TRAINABLE_VARIABLES` (see `tf.Variable`).
  96     name: A string, the name of the layer.
  97   """
  98 
  99   def __init__(self, rank,
 100                filters,
 101                kernel_size,
 102                strides=1,
 103                padding='valid',
 104                data_format=None,
 105                dilation_rate=1,
 106                activation=None,
 107                use_bias=True,
 108                kernel_initializer='glorot_uniform',
 109                bias_initializer='zeros',
 110                kernel_regularizer=None,
 111                bias_regularizer=None,
 112                activity_regularizer=None,
 113                kernel_constraint=None,
 114                bias_constraint=None,
 115                trainable=True,
 116                name=None,
 117                **kwargs):
 118     super(Conv, self).__init__(
 119         trainable=trainable,
 120         name=name,
 121         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
 122         **kwargs)
 123     self.rank = rank
 124     self.filters = filters
 125     self.kernel_size = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(
 126         kernel_size, rank, 'kernel_size')
 127     self.strides = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(strides, rank, 'strides')
 128     self.padding = conv_utils.normalize_padding(padding)
 129     if (self.padding == 'causal' and not isinstance(self,
 130                                                     (Conv1D, SeparableConv1D))):
 131       raise ValueError('Causal padding is only supported for `Conv1D`'
 132                        'and ``SeparableConv1D`.')
 133     self.data_format = conv_utils.normalize_data_format(data_format)
 134     self.dilation_rate = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(
 135         dilation_rate, rank, 'dilation_rate')
 136     self.activation = activations.get(activation)
 137     self.use_bias = use_bias
 138     self.kernel_initializer = initializers.get(kernel_initializer)
 139     self.bias_initializer = initializers.get(bias_initializer)
 140     self.kernel_regularizer = regularizers.get(kernel_regularizer)
 141     self.bias_regularizer = regularizers.get(bias_regularizer)
 142     self.kernel_constraint = constraints.get(kernel_constraint)
 143     self.bias_constraint = constraints.get(bias_constraint)
 144     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=self.rank + 2)
 145 
 146   def build(self, input_shape):
 147     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape)
 148     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 149       channel_axis = 1
 150     else:
 151       channel_axis = -1
 152     if input_shape[channel_axis].value is None:
 153       raise ValueError('The channel dimension of the inputs '
 154                        'should be defined. Found `None`.')
 155     input_dim = int(input_shape[channel_axis])
 156     kernel_shape = self.kernel_size + (input_dim, self.filters)
 157 
 158     self.kernel = self.add_weight(
 159         name='kernel',
 160         shape=kernel_shape,
 161         initializer=self.kernel_initializer,
 162         regularizer=self.kernel_regularizer,
 163         constraint=self.kernel_constraint,
 164         trainable=True,
 165         dtype=self.dtype)
 166     if self.use_bias:
 167       self.bias = self.add_weight(
 168           name='bias',
 169           shape=(self.filters,),
 170           initializer=self.bias_initializer,
 171           regularizer=self.bias_regularizer,
 172           constraint=self.bias_constraint,
 173           trainable=True,
 174           dtype=self.dtype)
 175     else:
 176       self.bias = None
 177     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=self.rank + 2,
 178                                 axes={channel_axis: input_dim})
 179     if self.padding == 'causal':
 180       op_padding = 'valid'
 181     else:
 182       op_padding = self.padding
 183     self._convolution_op = nn_ops.Convolution(
 184         input_shape,
 185         filter_shape=self.kernel.get_shape(),
 186         dilation_rate=self.dilation_rate,
 187         strides=self.strides,
 188         padding=op_padding.upper(),
 189         data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format,
 190                                                    self.rank + 2))
 191     self.built = True
 192 
 193   def call(self, inputs):
 194     outputs = self._convolution_op(inputs, self.kernel)
 195 
 196     if self.use_bias:
 197       if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 198         if self.rank == 1:
 199           # nn.bias_add does not accept a 1D input tensor.
 200           bias = array_ops.reshape(self.bias, (1, self.filters, 1))
 201           outputs += bias
 202         if self.rank == 2:
 203           outputs = nn.bias_add(outputs, self.bias, data_format='NCHW')
 204         if self.rank == 3:
 205           # As of Mar 2017, direct addition is significantly slower than
 206           # bias_add when computing gradients. To use bias_add, we collapse Z
 207           # and Y into a single dimension to obtain a 4D input tensor.
 208           outputs_shape = outputs.shape.as_list()
 209           if outputs_shape[0] is None:
 210             outputs_shape[0] = -1
 211           outputs_4d = array_ops.reshape(outputs,
 212                                          [outputs_shape[0], outputs_shape[1],
 213                                           outputs_shape[2] * outputs_shape[3],
 214                                           outputs_shape[4]])
 215           outputs_4d = nn.bias_add(outputs_4d, self.bias, data_format='NCHW')
 216           outputs = array_ops.reshape(outputs_4d, outputs_shape)
 217       else:
 218         outputs = nn.bias_add(outputs, self.bias, data_format='NHWC')
 219 
 220     if self.activation is not None:
 221       return self.activation(outputs)
 222     return outputs
 223 
 224   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
 225     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
 226     if self.data_format == 'channels_last':
 227       space = input_shape[1:-1]
 228       new_space = []
 229       for i in range(len(space)):
 230         new_dim = conv_utils.conv_output_length(
 231             space[i],
 232             self.kernel_size[i],
 233             padding=self.padding,
 234             stride=self.strides[i],
 235             dilation=self.dilation_rate[i])
 236         new_space.append(new_dim)
 237       return tensor_shape.TensorShape([input_shape[0]] + new_space +
 238                                       [self.filters])
 239     else:
 240       space = input_shape[2:]
 241       new_space = []
 242       for i in range(len(space)):
 243         new_dim = conv_utils.conv_output_length(
 244             space[i],
 245             self.kernel_size[i],
 246             padding=self.padding,
 247             stride=self.strides[i],
 248             dilation=self.dilation_rate[i])
 249         new_space.append(new_dim)
 250       return tensor_shape.TensorShape([input_shape[0], self.filters] +
 251                                       new_space)
 252 
 253   def get_config(self):
 254     config = {
 255         'filters': self.filters,
 256         'kernel_size': self.kernel_size,
 257         'strides': self.strides,
 258         'padding': self.padding,
 259         'data_format': self.data_format,
 260         'dilation_rate': self.dilation_rate,
 261         'activation': activations.serialize(self.activation),
 262         'use_bias': self.use_bias,
 263         'kernel_initializer': initializers.serialize(self.kernel_initializer),
 264         'bias_initializer': initializers.serialize(self.bias_initializer),
 265         'kernel_regularizer': regularizers.serialize(self.kernel_regularizer),
 266         'bias_regularizer': regularizers.serialize(self.bias_regularizer),
 267         'activity_regularizer':
 268             regularizers.serialize(self.activity_regularizer),
 269         'kernel_constraint': constraints.serialize(self.kernel_constraint),
 270         'bias_constraint': constraints.serialize(self.bias_constraint)
 271     }
 272     base_config = super(Conv, self).get_config()
 273     return dict(list(base_config.items()) + list(config.items()))
 274 
 275   def _compute_causal_padding(self):
 276     """Calculates padding for 'causal' option for 1-d conv layers."""
 277     left_pad = self.dilation_rate[0] * (self.kernel_size[0] - 1)
 278     if self.data_format == 'channels_last':
 279       causal_padding = [[0, 0], [left_pad, 0], [0, 0]]
 280     else:
 281       causal_padding = [[0, 0], [0, 0], [left_pad, 0]]
 282     return causal_padding
 283

 285 @tf_export('keras.layers.Conv1D', 'keras.layers.Convolution1D')
 286 class Conv1D(Conv):
 287   """1D convolution layer (e.g. temporal convolution).
 288 
 289   This layer creates a convolution kernel that is convolved
 290   with the layer input over a single spatial (or temporal) dimension
 291   to produce a tensor of outputs.
 292   If `use_bias` is True, a bias vector is created and added to the outputs.
 293   Finally, if `activation` is not `None`,
 294   it is applied to the outputs as well.
 295 
 296   When using this layer as the first layer in a model,
 297   provide an `input_shape` argument
 298   (tuple of integers or `None`, e.g.
 299   `(10, 128)` for sequences of 10 vectors of 128-dimensional vectors,
 300   or `(None, 128)` for variable-length sequences of 128-dimensional vectors.
 301 
 302   Arguments:
 303       filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space
 304           (i.e. the number of output filters in the convolution).
 305       kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of a single integer,
 306           specifying the length of the 1D convolution window.
 307       strides: An integer or tuple/list of a single integer,
 308           specifying the stride length of the convolution.
 309           Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
 310           any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
 311       padding: One of `"valid"`, `"causal"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
 312           `"causal"` results in causal (dilated) convolutions, e.g. output[t]
 313           does not depend on input[t+1:]. Useful when modeling temporal data
 314           where the model should not violate the temporal order.
 315           See [WaveNet: A Generative Model for Raw Audio, section
 316             2.1](https://arxiv.org/abs/1609.03499).
 317       data_format: A string,
 318           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
 319       dilation_rate: an integer or tuple/list of a single integer, specifying
 320           the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
 321           Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
 322           incompatible with specifying any `strides` value != 1.
 323       activation: Activation function to use.
 324           If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
 325           (ie. "linear" activation: `a(x) = x`).
 326       use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
 327       kernel_initializer: Initializer for the `kernel` weights matrix.
 328       bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
 329       kernel_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 330           the `kernel` weights matrix.
 331       bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
 332       activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 333           the output of the layer (its "activation")..
 334       kernel_constraint: Constraint function applied to the kernel matrix.
 335       bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
 336 
 337   Input shape:
 338       3D tensor with shape: `(batch_size, steps, input_dim)`
 339 
 340   Output shape:
 341       3D tensor with shape: `(batch_size, new_steps, filters)`
 342       `steps` value might have changed due to padding or strides.
 343   """
 344 
 345   def __init__(self,
 346                filters,
 347                kernel_size,
 348                strides=1,
 349                padding='valid',
 350                data_format='channels_last',
 351                dilation_rate=1,
 352                activation=None,
 353                use_bias=True,
 354                kernel_initializer='glorot_uniform',
 355                bias_initializer='zeros',
 356                kernel_regularizer=None,
 357                bias_regularizer=None,
 358                activity_regularizer=None,
 359                kernel_constraint=None,
 360                bias_constraint=None,
 361                **kwargs):
 362     super(Conv1D, self).__init__(
 363         rank=1,
 364         filters=filters,
 365         kernel_size=kernel_size,
 366         strides=strides,
 367         padding=padding,
 368         data_format=data_format,
 369         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
 370         activation=activations.get(activation),
 371         use_bias=use_bias,
 372         kernel_initializer=initializers.get(kernel_initializer),
 373         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
 374         kernel_regularizer=regularizers.get(kernel_regularizer),
 375         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
 376         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
 377         kernel_constraint=constraints.get(kernel_constraint),
 378         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
 379         **kwargs)
 380 
 381   def call(self, inputs):
 382     if self.padding == 'causal':
 383       inputs = array_ops.pad(inputs, self._compute_causal_padding())
 384     return super(Conv1D, self).call(inputs)
 385 
 386 
 387 @tf_export('keras.layers.Conv2D', 'keras.layers.Convolution2D')
 388 class Conv2D(Conv):
 389   """2D convolution layer (e.g. spatial convolution over images).
 390 
 391   This layer creates a convolution kernel that is convolved
 392   with the layer input to produce a tensor of
 393   outputs. If `use_bias` is True,
 394   a bias vector is created and added to the outputs. Finally, if
 395   `activation` is not `None`, it is applied to the outputs as well.
 396 
 397   When using this layer as the first layer in a model,
 398   provide the keyword argument `input_shape`
 399   (tuple of integers, does not include the sample axis),
 400   e.g. `input_shape=(128, 128, 3)` for 128x128 RGB pictures
 401   in `data_format="channels_last"`.
 402 
 403   Arguments:
 404       filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space
 405           (i.e. the number of output filters in the convolution).
 406       kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying the
 407           height and width of the 2D convolution window.
 408           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 409           all spatial dimensions.
 410       strides: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers,
 411           specifying the strides of the convolution along the height and width.
 412           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 413           all spatial dimensions.
 414           Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
 415           any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
 416       padding: one of `"valid"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
 417       data_format: A string,
 418           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
 419           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
 420           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
 421           `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
 422           corresponds to inputs with shape
 423           `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
 424           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
 425           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
 426           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
 427       dilation_rate: an integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying
 428           the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
 429           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 430           all spatial dimensions.
 431           Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
 432           incompatible with specifying any stride value != 1.
 433       activation: Activation function to use.
 434           If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
 435           (ie. "linear" activation: `a(x) = x`).
 436       use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
 437       kernel_initializer: Initializer for the `kernel` weights matrix.
 438       bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
 439       kernel_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 440           the `kernel` weights matrix.
 441       bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
 442       activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 443           the output of the layer (its "activation")..
 444       kernel_constraint: Constraint function applied to the kernel matrix.
 445       bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
 446 
 447   Input shape:
 448       4D tensor with shape:
 449       `(samples, channels, rows, cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
 450       or 4D tensor with shape:
 451       `(samples, rows, cols, channels)` if data_format='channels_last'.
 452 
 453   Output shape:
 454       4D tensor with shape:
 455       `(samples, filters, new_rows, new_cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
 456       or 4D tensor with shape:
 457       `(samples, new_rows, new_cols, filters)` if data_format='channels_last'.
 458       `rows` and `cols` values might have changed due to padding.
 459   """
 460 
 461   def __init__(self,
 462                filters,
 463                kernel_size,
 464                strides=(1, 1),
 465                padding='valid',
 466                data_format=None,
 467                dilation_rate=(1, 1),
 468                activation=None,
 469                use_bias=True,
 470                kernel_initializer='glorot_uniform',
 471                bias_initializer='zeros',
 472                kernel_regularizer=None,
 473                bias_regularizer=None,
 474                activity_regularizer=None,
 475                kernel_constraint=None,
 476                bias_constraint=None,
 477                **kwargs):
 478     super(Conv2D, self).__init__(
 479         rank=2,
 480         filters=filters,
 481         kernel_size=kernel_size,
 482         strides=strides,
 483         padding=padding,
 484         data_format=data_format,
 485         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
 486         activation=activations.get(activation),
 487         use_bias=use_bias,
 488         kernel_initializer=initializers.get(kernel_initializer),
 489         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
 490         kernel_regularizer=regularizers.get(kernel_regularizer),
 491         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
 492         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
 493         kernel_constraint=constraints.get(kernel_constraint),
 494         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
 495         **kwargs)
 496 
 497 
 498 @tf_export('keras.layers.Conv3D', 'keras.layers.Convolution3D')
 499 class Conv3D(Conv):
 500   """3D convolution layer (e.g. spatial convolution over volumes).
 501 
 502   This layer creates a convolution kernel that is convolved
 503   with the layer input to produce a tensor of
 504   outputs. If `use_bias` is True,
 505   a bias vector is created and added to the outputs. Finally, if
 506   `activation` is not `None`, it is applied to the outputs as well.
 507 
 508   When using this layer as the first layer in a model,
 509   provide the keyword argument `input_shape`
 510   (tuple of integers, does not include the sample axis),
 511   e.g. `input_shape=(128, 128, 128, 1)` for 128x128x128 volumes
 512   with a single channel,
 513   in `data_format="channels_last"`.
 514 
 515   Arguments:
 516       filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space
 517           (i.e. the number of output filters in the convolution).
 518       kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of 3 integers, specifying the
 519           depth, height and width of the 3D convolution window.
 520           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 521           all spatial dimensions.
 522       strides: An integer or tuple/list of 3 integers,
 523           specifying the strides of the convolution along each spatial
 524             dimension.
 525           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 526           all spatial dimensions.
 527           Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
 528           any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
 529       padding: one of `"valid"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
 530       data_format: A string,
 531           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
 532           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
 533           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
 534           `(batch, spatial_dim1, spatial_dim2, spatial_dim3, channels)`
 535           while `channels_first` corresponds to inputs with shape
 536           `(batch, channels, spatial_dim1, spatial_dim2, spatial_dim3)`.
 537           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
 538           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
 539           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
 540       dilation_rate: an integer or tuple/list of 3 integers, specifying
 541           the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
 542           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 543           all spatial dimensions.
 544           Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
 545           incompatible with specifying any stride value != 1.
 546       activation: Activation function to use.
 547           If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
 548           (ie. "linear" activation: `a(x) = x`).
 549       use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
 550       kernel_initializer: Initializer for the `kernel` weights matrix.
 551       bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
 552       kernel_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 553           the `kernel` weights matrix.
 554       bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
 555       activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 556           the output of the layer (its "activation")..
 557       kernel_constraint: Constraint function applied to the kernel matrix.
 558       bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
 559 
 560   Input shape:
 561       5D tensor with shape:
 562       `(samples, channels, conv_dim1, conv_dim2, conv_dim3)` if
 563         data_format='channels_first'
 564       or 5D tensor with shape:
 565       `(samples, conv_dim1, conv_dim2, conv_dim3, channels)` if
 566         data_format='channels_last'.
 567 
 568   Output shape:
 569       5D tensor with shape:
 570       `(samples, filters, new_conv_dim1, new_conv_dim2, new_conv_dim3)` if
 571         data_format='channels_first'
 572       or 5D tensor with shape:
 573       `(samples, new_conv_dim1, new_conv_dim2, new_conv_dim3, filters)` if
 574         data_format='channels_last'.
 575       `new_conv_dim1`, `new_conv_dim2` and `new_conv_dim3` values might have
 576         changed due to padding.
 577   """
 578 
 579   def __init__(self,
 580                filters,
 581                kernel_size,
 582                strides=(1, 1, 1),
 583                padding='valid',
 584                data_format=None,
 585                dilation_rate=(1, 1, 1),
 586                activation=None,
 587                use_bias=True,
 588                kernel_initializer='glorot_uniform',
 589                bias_initializer='zeros',
 590                kernel_regularizer=None,
 591                bias_regularizer=None,
 592                activity_regularizer=None,
 593                kernel_constraint=None,
 594                bias_constraint=None,
 595                **kwargs):
 596     super(Conv3D, self).__init__(
 597         rank=3,
 598         filters=filters,
 599         kernel_size=kernel_size,
 600         strides=strides,
 601         padding=padding,
 602         data_format=data_format,
 603         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
 604         activation=activations.get(activation),
 605         use_bias=use_bias,
 606         kernel_initializer=initializers.get(kernel_initializer),
 607         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
 608         kernel_regularizer=regularizers.get(kernel_regularizer),
 609         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
 610         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
 611         kernel_constraint=constraints.get(kernel_constraint),
 612         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
 613         **kwargs)

 616 @tf_export('keras.layers.Conv2DTranspose',
 617            'keras.layers.Convolution2DTranspose')
 618 class Conv2DTranspose(Conv2D):
 619   """Transposed convolution layer (sometimes called Deconvolution).
 620 
 621   The need for transposed convolutions generally arises
 622   from the desire to use a transformation going in the opposite direction
 623   of a normal convolution, i.e., from something that has the shape of the
 624   output of some convolution to something that has the shape of its input
 625   while maintaining a connectivity pattern that is compatible with
 626   said convolution.
 627 
 628   When using this layer as the first layer in a model,
 629   provide the keyword argument `input_shape`
 630   (tuple of integers, does not include the sample axis),
 631   e.g. `input_shape=(128, 128, 3)` for 128x128 RGB pictures
 632   in `data_format="channels_last"`.
 633 
 634   Arguments:
 635       filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space
 636           (i.e. the number of output filters in the convolution).
 637       kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying the
 638           height and width of the 2D convolution window.
 639           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 640           all spatial dimensions.
 641       strides: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers,
 642           specifying the strides of the convolution along the height and width.
 643           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 644           all spatial dimensions.
 645           Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
 646           any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
 647       padding: one of `"valid"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
 648       data_format: A string,
 649           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
 650           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
 651           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
 652           `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
 653           corresponds to inputs with shape
 654           `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
 655           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
 656           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
 657           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
 658       dilation_rate: an integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying
 659           the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
 660           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
 661           all spatial dimensions.
 662           Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
 663           incompatible with specifying any stride value != 1.
 664       activation: Activation function to use.
 665           If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
 666           (ie. "linear" activation: `a(x) = x`).
 667       use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
 668       kernel_initializer: Initializer for the `kernel` weights matrix.
 669       bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
 670       kernel_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 671           the `kernel` weights matrix.
 672       bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
 673       activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
 674           the output of the layer (its "activation")..
 675       kernel_constraint: Constraint function applied to the kernel matrix.
 676       bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
 677 
 678   Input shape:
 679       4D tensor with shape:
 680       `(batch, channels, rows, cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
 681       or 4D tensor with shape:
 682       `(batch, rows, cols, channels)` if data_format='channels_last'.
 683 
 684   Output shape:
 685       4D tensor with shape:
 686       `(batch, filters, new_rows, new_cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
 687       or 4D tensor with shape:
 688       `(batch, new_rows, new_cols, filters)` if data_format='channels_last'.
 689       `rows` and `cols` values might have changed due to padding.
 690 
 691   References:
 692       - [A guide to convolution arithmetic for deep
 693         learning](https://arxiv.org/abs/1603.07285v1)
 694       - [Deconvolutional
 695         Networks](http://www.matthewzeiler.com/pubs/cvpr2010/cvpr2010.pdf)
 696   """
 697 
 698   def __init__(self,
 699                filters,
 700                kernel_size,
 701                strides=(1, 1),
 702                padding='valid',
 703                data_format=None,
 704                activation=None,
 705                use_bias=True,
 706                kernel_initializer='glorot_uniform',
 707                bias_initializer='zeros',
 708                kernel_regularizer=None,
 709                bias_regularizer=None,
 710                activity_regularizer=None,
 711                kernel_constraint=None,
 712                bias_constraint=None,
 713                **kwargs):
 714     super(Conv2DTranspose, self).__init__(
 715         filters=filters,
 716         kernel_size=kernel_size,
 717         strides=strides,
 718         padding=padding,
 719         data_format=data_format,
 720         activation=activations.get(activation),
 721         use_bias=use_bias,
 722         kernel_initializer=initializers.get(kernel_initializer),
 723         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
 724         kernel_regularizer=regularizers.get(kernel_regularizer),
 725         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
 726         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
 727         kernel_constraint=constraints.get(kernel_constraint),
 728         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
 729         **kwargs)
 730 
 731   def build(self, input_shape):
 732     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape)
 733     if len(input_shape) != 4:
 734       raise ValueError('Inputs should have rank 4. Received input shape: ' +
 735                        str(input_shape))
 736     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 737       channel_axis = 1
 738     else:
 739       channel_axis = -1
 740     if input_shape[channel_axis].value is None:
 741       raise ValueError('The channel dimension of the inputs '
 742                        'should be defined. Found `None`.')
 743     input_dim = int(input_shape[channel_axis])
 744     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=4, axes={channel_axis: input_dim})
 745     kernel_shape = self.kernel_size + (self.filters, input_dim)
 746 
 747     self.kernel = self.add_weight(
 748         name='kernel',
 749         shape=kernel_shape,
 750         initializer=self.kernel_initializer,
 751         regularizer=self.kernel_regularizer,
 752         constraint=self.kernel_constraint,
 753         trainable=True,
 754         dtype=self.dtype)
 755     if self.use_bias:
 756       self.bias = self.add_weight(
 757           name='bias',
 758           shape=(self.filters,),
 759           initializer=self.bias_initializer,
 760           regularizer=self.bias_regularizer,
 761           constraint=self.bias_constraint,
 762           trainable=True,
 763           dtype=self.dtype)
 764     else:
 765       self.bias = None
 766     self.built = True
 767 
 768   def call(self, inputs):
 769     inputs_shape = array_ops.shape(inputs)
 770     batch_size = inputs_shape[0]
 771     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 772       c_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 1, 2, 3
 773     else:
 774       c_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 3, 1, 2
 775 
 776     height, width = inputs_shape[h_axis], inputs_shape[w_axis]
 777     kernel_h, kernel_w = self.kernel_size
 778     stride_h, stride_w = self.strides
 779 
 780     # Infer the dynamic output shape:
 781     out_height = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(height,
 782                                                  kernel_h,
 783                                                  self.padding,
 784                                                  stride_h)
 785     out_width = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(width,
 786                                                 kernel_w,
 787                                                 self.padding,
 788                                                 stride_w)
 789     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 790       output_shape = (batch_size, self.filters, out_height, out_width)
 791       strides = (1, 1, stride_h, stride_w)
 792     else:
 793       output_shape = (batch_size, out_height, out_width, self.filters)
 794       strides = (1, stride_h, stride_w, 1)
 795 
 796     output_shape_tensor = array_ops.stack(output_shape)
 797     outputs = nn.conv2d_transpose(
 798         inputs,
 799         self.kernel,
 800         output_shape_tensor,
 801         strides,
 802         padding=self.padding.upper(),
 803         data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
 804 
 805     if not context.executing_eagerly():
 806       # Infer the static output shape:
 807       out_shape = inputs.get_shape().as_list()
 808       out_shape[c_axis] = self.filters
 809       out_shape[h_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(out_shape[h_axis],
 810                                                           kernel_h,
 811                                                           self.padding,
 812                                                           stride_h)
 813       out_shape[w_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(out_shape[w_axis],
 814                                                           kernel_w,
 815                                                           self.padding,
 816                                                           stride_w)
 817       outputs.set_shape(out_shape)
 818 
 819     if self.use_bias:
 820       outputs = nn.bias_add(
 821           outputs,
 822           self.bias,
 823           data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
 824 
 825     if self.activation is not None:
 826       return self.activation(outputs)
 827     return outputs
 828 
 829   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
 830     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
 831     output_shape = list(input_shape)
 832     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
 833       c_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 1, 2, 3
 834     else:
 835       c_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 3, 1, 2
 836 
 837     kernel_h, kernel_w = self.kernel_size
 838     stride_h, stride_w = self.strides
 839 
 840     output_shape[c_axis] = self.filters
 841     output_shape[h_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(
 842         output_shape[h_axis], kernel_h, self.padding, stride_h)
 843     output_shape[w_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(
 844         output_shape[w_axis], kernel_w, self.padding, stride_w)
 845     return tensor_shape.TensorShape(output_shape)
 846

1002           initializer=self.bias_initializer,

1013     batch_size = inputs_shape[0]

1015       c_axis, d_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 1, 2, 3, 4
1016     else:
1017       c_axis, d_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 4, 1, 2, 3
1018 
1019     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=5, axes={c_axis: inputs_shape[c_axis]})
1020 
1021     depth = inputs_shape[d_axis]
1022     height = inputs_shape[h_axis]
1023     width = inputs_shape[w_axis]
1024 
1025     kernel_d, kernel_h, kernel_w = self.kernel_size
1026     stride_d, stride_h, stride_w = self.strides
1027

1030                                                 kernel_d,
1031                                                 self.padding,
1032                                                 stride_d)
1033     out_height = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(height,
1034                                                  kernel_h,
1035                                                  self.padding,
1036                                                  stride_h)
1037     out_width = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(width,
1038                                                 kernel_w,
1039                                                 self.padding,
1040                                                 stride_w)
1041     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1042       output_shape = (batch_size, self.filters, out_depth, out_height,
1043                       out_width)
1044       strides = (1, 1, stride_d, stride_h, stride_w)
1045     else:
1046       output_shape = (batch_size, out_depth, out_height, out_width,
1047                       self.filters)
1048       strides = (1, stride_d, stride_h, stride_w, 1)
1049

1051     outputs = nn.conv3d_transpose(
1052         inputs,
1053         self.kernel,
1054         output_shape_tensor,
1055         strides,
1056         data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=5),
1057         padding=self.padding.upper())

1062       out_shape[c_axis] = self.filters
1063       out_shape[d_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(out_shape[d_axis],
1064                                                           kernel_d,
1065                                                           self.padding,
1066                                                           stride_d)

1068                                                           kernel_h,
1069                                                           self.padding,

1072                                                           kernel_w,

1083             outputs_shape[0], outputs_shape[1],
1084             outputs_shape[2] * outputs_shape[3], outputs_shape[4]

1086       else:

1088             outputs_shape[0], outputs_shape[1] * outputs_shape[2],
1089             outputs_shape[3], outputs_shape[4]
1090         ])

1092           outputs_4d,
1093           self.bias,
1094           data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
1095       outputs = array_ops.reshape(outputs_4d, outputs_shape)
1096 
1097     if self.activation is not None:
1098       return self.activation(outputs)
1099     return outputs
1100 
1101   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
1102     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
1103     output_shape = list(input_shape)
1104     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1105       c_axis, d_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 1, 2, 3, 4
1106     else:
1107       c_axis, d_axis, h_axis, w_axis = 4, 1, 2, 3
1108 
1109     kernel_d, kernel_h, kernel_w = self.kernel_size
1110     stride_d, stride_h, stride_w = self.strides
1111 
1112     output_shape[c_axis] = self.filters
1113     output_shape[d_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(
1114         output_shape[d_axis], kernel_d, self.padding, stride_d)
1115     output_shape[h_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(
1116         output_shape[h_axis], kernel_h, self.padding, stride_h)
1117     output_shape[w_axis] = conv_utils.deconv_output_length(
1118         output_shape[w_axis], kernel_w, self.padding, stride_w)
1119     return tensor_shape.TensorShape(output_shape)
1120 
1121 
1122 class SeparableConv(Conv):
1123   """Abstract base layer for separable nD convolution.
1124 
1125   This layer performs a depthwise convolution that acts separately on
1126   channels, followed by a pointwise convolution that mixes channels.
1127   If `use_bias` is True and a bias initializer is provided,
1128   it adds a bias vector to the output.
1129   It then optionally applies an activation function to produce the final output.
1130 
1131   Arguments:
1132     rank: An integer, the rank of the convolution, e.g. "2" for 2D convolution.
1133     filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space (i.e. the number
1134       of filters in the convolution).
1135     kernel_size: A tuple or list of integers specifying the spatial
1136       dimensions of the filters. Can be a single integer to specify the same
1137       value for all spatial dimensions.
1138     strides: A tuple or list of integers specifying the strides
1139       of the convolution. Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
1140       all spatial dimensions.
1141       Specifying any `stride` value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
1142       any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
1143     padding: One of `"valid"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
1144     data_format: A string, one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
1145       The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
1146       `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
1147       `(batch, ..., channels)` while `channels_first` corresponds to
1148       inputs with shape `(batch, channels, ...)`.
1149     dilation_rate: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying
1150       the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
1151       Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
1152       all spatial dimensions.
1153       Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
1154       incompatible with specifying any stride value != 1.
1155     depth_multiplier: The number of depthwise convolution output channels for
1156       each input channel. The total number of depthwise convolution output
1157       channels will be equal to `num_filters_in * depth_multiplier`.
1158     activation: Activation function. Set it to None to maintain a
1159       linear activation.
1160     use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias.
1161     depthwise_initializer: An initializer for the depthwise convolution kernel.
1162     pointwise_initializer: An initializer for the pointwise convolution kernel.
1163     bias_initializer: An initializer for the bias vector. If None, the default
1164       initializer will be used.
1165     depthwise_regularizer: Optional regularizer for the depthwise
1166       convolution kernel.
1167     pointwise_regularizer: Optional regularizer for the pointwise
1168       convolution kernel.
1169     bias_regularizer: Optional regularizer for the bias vector.
1170     activity_regularizer: Optional regularizer function for the output.
1171     depthwise_constraint: Optional projection function to be applied to the
1172         depthwise kernel after being updated by an `Optimizer` (e.g. used for
1173         norm constraints or value constraints for layer weights). The function
1174         must take as input the unprojected variable and must return the
1175         projected variable (which must have the same shape). Constraints are
1176         not safe to use when doing asynchronous distributed training.
1177     pointwise_constraint: Optional projection function to be applied to the
1178         pointwise kernel after being updated by an `Optimizer`.
1179     bias_constraint: Optional projection function to be applied to the
1180         bias after being updated by an `Optimizer`.
1181     trainable: Boolean, if `True` also add variables to the graph collection
1182       `GraphKeys.TRAINABLE_VARIABLES` (see `tf.Variable`).
1183     name: A string, the name of the layer.
1184   """
1185 
1186   def __init__(self,
1187                rank,
1188                filters,
1189                kernel_size,
1190                strides=1,
1191                padding='valid',
1192                data_format=None,
1193                dilation_rate=1,
1194                depth_multiplier=1,
1195                activation=None,
1196                use_bias=True,
1197                depthwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1198                pointwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1199                bias_initializer='zeros',
1200                depthwise_regularizer=None,
1201                pointwise_regularizer=None,
1202                bias_regularizer=None,
1203                activity_regularizer=None,
1204                depthwise_constraint=None,
1205                pointwise_constraint=None,
1206                bias_constraint=None,
1207                trainable=True,
1208                name=None,
1209                **kwargs):
1210     super(SeparableConv, self).__init__(
1211         rank=rank,
1212         filters=filters,
1213         kernel_size=kernel_size,
1214         strides=strides,
1215         padding=padding,
1216         data_format=data_format,
1217         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
1218         activation=activations.get(activation),
1219         use_bias=use_bias,
1220         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
1221         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
1222         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
1223         bias_constraint=bias_constraint,
1224         trainable=trainable,
1225         name=name,
1226         **kwargs)
1227     self.depth_multiplier = depth_multiplier
1228     self.depthwise_initializer = initializers.get(depthwise_initializer)
1229     self.pointwise_initializer = initializers.get(pointwise_initializer)
1230     self.depthwise_regularizer = regularizers.get(depthwise_regularizer)
1231     self.pointwise_regularizer = regularizers.get(pointwise_regularizer)
1232     self.depthwise_constraint = constraints.get(depthwise_constraint)
1233     self.pointwise_constraint = constraints.get(pointwise_constraint)
1234 
1235   def build(self, input_shape):
1236     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape)
1237     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1238       channel_axis = 1
1239     else:
1240       channel_axis = -1
1241     if input_shape[channel_axis].value is None:
1242       raise ValueError('The channel dimension of the inputs '
1243                        'should be defined. Found `None`.')
1244     input_dim = int(input_shape[channel_axis])
1245     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=self.rank + 2,
1246                                 axes={channel_axis: input_dim})
1247     depthwise_kernel_shape = self.kernel_size + (input_dim,
1248                                                  self.depth_multiplier)
1249     pointwise_kernel_shape = (
1250         1,) * self.rank + (self.depth_multiplier * input_dim, self.filters)
1251 
1252     self.depthwise_kernel = self.add_weight(
1253         name='depthwise_kernel',
1254         shape=depthwise_kernel_shape,
1255         initializer=self.depthwise_initializer,
1256         regularizer=self.depthwise_regularizer,
1257         constraint=self.depthwise_constraint,
1258         trainable=True,
1259         dtype=self.dtype)
1260     self.pointwise_kernel = self.add_weight(
1261         name='pointwise_kernel',
1262         shape=pointwise_kernel_shape,
1263         initializer=self.pointwise_initializer,
1264         regularizer=self.pointwise_regularizer,
1265         constraint=self.pointwise_constraint,
1266         trainable=True,
1267         dtype=self.dtype)
1268     if self.use_bias:
1269       self.bias = self.add_weight(
1270           name='bias',
1271           shape=(self.filters,),
1272           initializer=self.bias_initializer,
1273           regularizer=self.bias_regularizer,
1274           constraint=self.bias_constraint,
1275           trainable=True,
1276           dtype=self.dtype)
1277     else:
1278       self.bias = None
1279     self.built = True
1280 
1281   def call(self, inputs):
1282     raise NotImplementedError
1283

1288         'kernel_size':

1290         'strides':

1292         'padding':
1293             self.padding,
1294         'data_format':
1295             self.data_format,
1296         'depth_multiplier':
1297             self.depth_multiplier,
1298         'dilation_rate':
1299             self.dilation_rate,
1300         'activation':
1301             activations.serialize(self.activation),
1302         'use_bias':
1303             self.use_bias,
1304         'depthwise_initializer':
1305             initializers.serialize(self.depthwise_initializer),
1306         'pointwise_initializer':
1307             initializers.serialize(self.pointwise_initializer),
1308         'bias_initializer':
1309             initializers.serialize(self.bias_initializer),
1310         'depthwise_regularizer':
1311             regularizers.serialize(self.depthwise_regularizer),
1312         'pointwise_regularizer':
1313             regularizers.serialize(self.pointwise_regularizer),
1314         'bias_regularizer':
1315             regularizers.serialize(self.bias_regularizer),
1316         'activity_regularizer':
1317             regularizers.serialize(self.activity_regularizer),
1318         'depthwise_constraint':
1319             constraints.serialize(self.depthwise_constraint),
1320         'pointwise_constraint':
1321             constraints.serialize(self.pointwise_constraint),

1390   def __init__(self,
1391                filters,
1392                kernel_size,
1393                strides=1,
1394                padding='valid',
1395                data_format=None,
1396                dilation_rate=1,
1397                depth_multiplier=1,
1398                activation=None,
1399                use_bias=True,
1400                depthwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1401                pointwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1402                bias_initializer='zeros',
1403                depthwise_regularizer=None,
1404                pointwise_regularizer=None,
1405                bias_regularizer=None,
1406                activity_regularizer=None,
1407                depthwise_constraint=None,
1408                pointwise_constraint=None,
1409                bias_constraint=None,
1410                **kwargs):
1411     super(SeparableConv1D, self).__init__(
1412         rank=1,
1413         filters=filters,
1414         kernel_size=kernel_size,
1415         strides=strides,
1416         padding=padding,
1417         data_format=data_format,
1418         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
1419         depth_multiplier=depth_multiplier,
1420         activation=activations.get(activation),
1421         use_bias=use_bias,
1422         depthwise_initializer=initializers.get(depthwise_initializer),
1423         pointwise_initializer=initializers.get(pointwise_initializer),
1424         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
1425         depthwise_regularizer=regularizers.get(depthwise_regularizer),
1426         pointwise_regularizer=regularizers.get(pointwise_regularizer),
1427         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
1428         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
1429         depthwise_constraint=constraints.get(depthwise_constraint),
1430         pointwise_constraint=constraints.get(pointwise_constraint),
1431         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
1432         **kwargs)
1433 
1434   def call(self, inputs):
1435     if self.padding == 'causal':
1436       inputs = array_ops.pad(inputs, self._compute_causal_padding())
1437     if self.data_format == 'channels_last':
1438       strides = (1,) + self.strides * 2 + (1,)
1439       spatial_start_dim = 1
1440     else:
1441       strides = (1, 1) + self.strides * 2
1442       spatial_start_dim = 2
1443 
1444     # Explicitly broadcast inputs and kernels to 4D.
1445     # TODO(fchollet): refactor when a native separable_conv1d op is available.
1446     inputs = array_ops.expand_dims(inputs, spatial_start_dim)
1447     depthwise_kernel = array_ops.expand_dims(self.depthwise_kernel, 0)
1448     pointwise_kernel = array_ops.expand_dims(self.pointwise_kernel, 0)
1449     dilation_rate = (1,) + self.dilation_rate
1450 
1451     if self.padding == 'causal':
1452       op_padding = 'valid'
1453     else:
1454       op_padding = self.padding
1455     outputs = nn.separable_conv2d(
1456         inputs,
1457         depthwise_kernel,
1458         pointwise_kernel,
1459         strides=strides,
1460         padding=op_padding.upper(),
1461         rate=dilation_rate,
1462         data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
1463 
1464     if self.use_bias:
1465       outputs = nn.bias_add(
1466           outputs,
1467           self.bias,
1468           data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
1469 
1470     outputs = array_ops.squeeze(outputs, [spatial_start_dim])
1471 
1472     if self.activation is not None:
1473       return self.activation(outputs)
1474     return outputs

1477 @tf_export('keras.layers.SeparableConv2D',
1478            'keras.layers.SeparableConvolution2D')
1479 class SeparableConv2D(SeparableConv):
1480   """Depthwise separable 2D convolution.
1481 
1482   Separable convolutions consist in first performing
1483   a depthwise spatial convolution
1484   (which acts on each input channel separately)
1485   followed by a pointwise convolution which mixes together the resulting
1486   output channels. The `depth_multiplier` argument controls how many
1487   output channels are generated per input channel in the depthwise step.
1488 
1489   Intuitively, separable convolutions can be understood as
1490   a way to factorize a convolution kernel into two smaller kernels,
1491   or as an extreme version of an Inception block.
1492 
1493   Arguments:
1494       filters: Integer, the dimensionality of the output space
1495           (i.e. the number of output filters in the convolution).
1496       kernel_size: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying the
1497           height and width of the 2D convolution window.
1498           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
1499           all spatial dimensions.
1500       strides: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers,
1501           specifying the strides of the convolution along the height and width.
1502           Can be a single integer to specify the same value for
1503           all spatial dimensions.
1504           Specifying any stride value != 1 is incompatible with specifying
1505           any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
1506       padding: one of `"valid"` or `"same"` (case-insensitive).
1507       data_format: A string,
1508           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
1509           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
1510           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
1511           `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
1512           corresponds to inputs with shape
1513           `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
1514           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
1515           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
1516           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
1517       dilation_rate: An integer or tuple/list of 2 integers, specifying
1518           the dilation rate to use for dilated convolution.
1519           Currently, specifying any `dilation_rate` value != 1 is
1520           incompatible with specifying any `strides` value != 1.
1521       depth_multiplier: The number of depthwise convolution output channels
1522           for each input channel.
1523           The total number of depthwise convolution output
1524           channels will be equal to `filters_in * depth_multiplier`.
1525       activation: Activation function to use.
1526           If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
1527           (ie. "linear" activation: `a(x) = x`).
1528       use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
1529       depthwise_initializer: Initializer for the depthwise kernel matrix.
1530       pointwise_initializer: Initializer for the pointwise kernel matrix.
1531       bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
1532       depthwise_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
1533           the depthwise kernel matrix.
1534       pointwise_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
1535           the pointwise kernel matrix.
1536       bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
1537       activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
1538           the output of the layer (its "activation")..
1539       depthwise_constraint: Constraint function applied to
1540           the depthwise kernel matrix.
1541       pointwise_constraint: Constraint function applied to
1542           the pointwise kernel matrix.
1543       bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
1544 
1545   Input shape:
1546       4D tensor with shape:
1547       `(batch, channels, rows, cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
1548       or 4D tensor with shape:
1549       `(batch, rows, cols, channels)` if data_format='channels_last'.
1550 
1551   Output shape:
1552       4D tensor with shape:
1553       `(batch, filters, new_rows, new_cols)` if data_format='channels_first'
1554       or 4D tensor with shape:
1555       `(batch, new_rows, new_cols, filters)` if data_format='channels_last'.
1556       `rows` and `cols` values might have changed due to padding.
1557   """
1558 
1559   def __init__(self,
1560                filters,
1561                kernel_size,
1562                strides=(1, 1),
1563                padding='valid',
1564                data_format=None,
1565                dilation_rate=(1, 1),
1566                depth_multiplier=1,
1567                activation=None,
1568                use_bias=True,
1569                depthwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1570                pointwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1571                bias_initializer='zeros',
1572                depthwise_regularizer=None,
1573                pointwise_regularizer=None,
1574                bias_regularizer=None,
1575                activity_regularizer=None,
1576                depthwise_constraint=None,
1577                pointwise_constraint=None,
1578                bias_constraint=None,
1579                **kwargs):
1580     super(SeparableConv2D, self).__init__(
1581         rank=2,
1582         filters=filters,
1583         kernel_size=kernel_size,
1584         strides=strides,
1585         padding=padding,
1586         data_format=data_format,
1587         dilation_rate=dilation_rate,
1588         depth_multiplier=depth_multiplier,
1589         activation=activations.get(activation),
1590         use_bias=use_bias,
1591         depthwise_initializer=initializers.get(depthwise_initializer),
1592         pointwise_initializer=initializers.get(pointwise_initializer),
1593         bias_initializer=initializers.get(bias_initializer),
1594         depthwise_regularizer=regularizers.get(depthwise_regularizer),
1595         pointwise_regularizer=regularizers.get(pointwise_regularizer),
1596         bias_regularizer=regularizers.get(bias_regularizer),
1597         activity_regularizer=regularizers.get(activity_regularizer),
1598         depthwise_constraint=constraints.get(depthwise_constraint),
1599         pointwise_constraint=constraints.get(pointwise_constraint),
1600         bias_constraint=constraints.get(bias_constraint),
1601         **kwargs)
1602 
1603   def call(self, inputs):
1604     # Apply the actual ops.
1605     if self.data_format == 'channels_last':
1606       strides = (1,) + self.strides + (1,)
1607     else:
1608       strides = (1, 1) + self.strides
1609     outputs = nn.separable_conv2d(
1610         inputs,
1611         self.depthwise_kernel,
1612         self.pointwise_kernel,
1613         strides=strides,
1614         padding=self.padding.upper(),
1615         rate=self.dilation_rate,
1616         data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
1617 
1618     if self.use_bias:
1619       outputs = nn.bias_add(
1620           outputs,
1621           self.bias,
1622           data_format=conv_utils.convert_data_format(self.data_format, ndim=4))
1623 
1624     if self.activation is not None:
1625       return self.activation(outputs)
1626     return outputs

1629 @tf_export('keras.layers.DepthwiseConv2D')
1630 class DepthwiseConv2D(Conv2D):

1645         specifying the strides of the convolution along the height and width.
1646         Can be a single integer to specify the same value for

1649         any `dilation_rate` value != 1.
1650     padding: one of `'valid'` or `'same'` (case-insensitive).
1651     depth_multiplier: The number of depthwise convolution output channels
1652         for each input channel.
1653         The total number of depthwise convolution output
1654         channels will be equal to `filters_in * depth_multiplier`.
1655     data_format: A string,
1656         one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
1657         The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
1658         `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
1659         `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
1660         corresponds to inputs with shape
1661         `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
1662         It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
1663         Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
1664         If you never set it, then it will be 'channels_last'.
1665     activation: Activation function to use.
1666         If you don't specify anything, no activation is applied
1667         (ie. 'linear' activation: `a(x) = x`).
1668     use_bias: Boolean, whether the layer uses a bias vector.
1669     depthwise_initializer: Initializer for the depthwise kernel matrix.
1670     bias_initializer: Initializer for the bias vector.
1671     depthwise_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
1672         the depthwise kernel matrix.
1673     bias_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to the bias vector.
1674     activity_regularizer: Regularizer function applied to
1675         the output of the layer (its 'activation').
1676     depthwise_constraint: Constraint function applied to
1677         the depthwise kernel matrix.
1678     bias_constraint: Constraint function applied to the bias vector.
1679 
1680   Input shape:
1681     4D tensor with shape:
1682     `[batch, channels, rows, cols]` if data_format='channels_first'
1683     or 4D tensor with shape:
1684     `[batch, rows, cols, channels]` if data_format='channels_last'.
1685 
1686   Output shape:
1687     4D tensor with shape:
1688     `[batch, filters, new_rows, new_cols]` if data_format='channels_first'
1689     or 4D tensor with shape:
1690     `[batch, new_rows, new_cols, filters]` if data_format='channels_last'.
1691     `rows` and `cols` values might have changed due to padding.
1692   """
1693 
1694   def __init__(self,
1695                kernel_size,
1696                strides=(1, 1),
1697                padding='valid',
1698                depth_multiplier=1,
1699                data_format=None,
1700                activation=None,
1701                use_bias=True,
1702                depthwise_initializer='glorot_uniform',
1703                bias_initializer='zeros',
1704                depthwise_regularizer=None,
1705                bias_regularizer=None,
1706                activity_regularizer=None,
1707                depthwise_constraint=None,
1708                bias_constraint=None,
1709                **kwargs):
1710     super(DepthwiseConv2D, self).__init__(
1711         filters=None,
1712         kernel_size=kernel_size,
1713         strides=strides,
1714         padding=padding,
1715         data_format=data_format,
1716         activation=activation,
1717         use_bias=use_bias,
1718         bias_regularizer=bias_regularizer,
1719         activity_regularizer=activity_regularizer,
1720         bias_constraint=bias_constraint,
1721         **kwargs)
1722     self.depth_multiplier = depth_multiplier
1723     self.depthwise_initializer = initializers.get(depthwise_initializer)
1724     self.depthwise_regularizer = regularizers.get(depthwise_regularizer)
1725     self.depthwise_constraint = constraints.get(depthwise_constraint)
1726     self.bias_initializer = initializers.get(bias_initializer)
1727 
1728   def build(self, input_shape):
1729     if len(input_shape) < 4:
1730       raise ValueError('Inputs to `DepthwiseConv2D` should have rank 4. '
1731                        'Received input shape:', str(input_shape))
1732     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1733       channel_axis = 1
1734     else:
1735       channel_axis = 3
1736     if input_shape[channel_axis] is None:
1737       raise ValueError('The channel dimension of the inputs to '
1738                        '`DepthwiseConv2D` '
1739                        'should be defined. Found `None`.')
1740     input_dim = int(input_shape[channel_axis])
1741     depthwise_kernel_shape = (self.kernel_size[0],
1742                               self.kernel_size[1],
1743                               input_dim,
1744                               self.depth_multiplier)
1745 
1746     self.depthwise_kernel = self.add_weight(
1747         shape=depthwise_kernel_shape,
1748         initializer=self.depthwise_initializer,
1749         name='depthwise_kernel',
1750         regularizer=self.depthwise_regularizer,
1751         constraint=self.depthwise_constraint)
1752 
1753     if self.use_bias:
1754       self.bias = self.add_weight(shape=(input_dim * self.depth_multiplier,),
1755                                   initializer=self.bias_initializer,
1756                                   name='bias',
1757                                   regularizer=self.bias_regularizer,
1758                                   constraint=self.bias_constraint)
1759     else:
1760       self.bias = None
1761     # Set input spec.
1762     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=4, axes={channel_axis: input_dim})
1763     self.built = True
1764 
1765   def call(self, inputs, training=None):
1766     outputs = backend.depthwise_conv2d(
1767         inputs,
1768         self.depthwise_kernel,
1769         strides=self.strides,
1770         padding=self.padding,
1771         dilation_rate=self.dilation_rate,
1772         data_format=self.data_format)
1773 
1774     if self.use_bias:
1775       outputs = backend.bias_add(
1776           outputs,
1777           self.bias,
1778           data_format=self.data_format)
1779 
1780     if self.activation is not None:
1781       return self.activation(outputs)
1782 
1783     return outputs
1784 
1785   @tf_utils.shape_type_conversion
1786   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
1787     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1788       rows = input_shape[2]
1789       cols = input_shape[3]
1790       out_filters = input_shape[1] * self.depth_multiplier
1791     elif self.data_format == 'channels_last':
1792       rows = input_shape[1]
1793       cols = input_shape[2]
1794       out_filters = input_shape[3] * self.depth_multiplier
1795 
1796     rows = conv_utils.conv_output_length(rows, self.kernel_size[0],
1797                                          self.padding,
1798                                          self.strides[0])
1799     cols = conv_utils.conv_output_length(cols, self.kernel_size[1],
1800                                          self.padding,
1801                                          self.strides[1])
1802     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
1803       return (input_shape[0], out_filters, rows, cols)
1804     elif self.data_format == 'channels_last':
1805       return (input_shape[0], rows, cols, out_filters)
1806 
1807   def get_config(self):
1808     config = super(DepthwiseConv2D, self).get_config()
1809     config.pop('filters')
1810     config.pop('kernel_initializer')
1811     config.pop('kernel_regularizer')
1812     config.pop('kernel_constraint')
1813     config['depth_multiplier'] = self.depth_multiplier
1814     config['depthwise_initializer'] = initializers.serialize(
1815         self.depthwise_initializer)
1816     config['depthwise_regularizer'] = regularizers.serialize(
1817         self.depthwise_regularizer)
1818     config['depthwise_constraint'] = constraints.serialize(
1819         self.depthwise_constraint)
1820     return config

2042 @tf_export('keras.layers.ZeroPadding2D')
2043 class ZeroPadding2D(Layer):
2044   """Zero-padding layer for 2D input (e.g. picture).
2045 
2046   This layer can add rows and columns of zeros
2047   at the top, bottom, left and right side of an image tensor.
2048 
2049   Arguments:
2050       padding: int, or tuple of 2 ints, or tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints.
2051           - If int: the same symmetric padding
2052               is applied to height and width.
2053           - If tuple of 2 ints:
2054               interpreted as two different
2055               symmetric padding values for height and width:
2056               `(symmetric_height_pad, symmetric_width_pad)`.
2057           - If tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints:
2058               interpreted as
2059               `((top_pad, bottom_pad), (left_pad, right_pad))`
2060       data_format: A string,
2061           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
2062           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
2063           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
2064           `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
2065           corresponds to inputs with shape
2066           `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
2067           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
2068           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
2069           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
2070 
2071   Input shape:
2072       4D tensor with shape:
2073       - If `data_format` is `"channels_last"`:
2074           `(batch, rows, cols, channels)`
2075       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2076           `(batch, channels, rows, cols)`
2077 
2078   Output shape:
2079       4D tensor with shape:
2080       - If `data_format` is `"channels_last"`:
2081           `(batch, padded_rows, padded_cols, channels)`
2082       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2083           `(batch, channels, padded_rows, padded_cols)`
2084   """
2085 
2086   def __init__(self, padding=(1, 1), data_format=None, **kwargs):
2087     super(ZeroPadding2D, self).__init__(**kwargs)
2088     self.data_format = conv_utils.normalize_data_format(data_format)
2089     if isinstance(padding, int):
2090       self.padding = ((padding, padding), (padding, padding))
2091     elif hasattr(padding, '__len__'):
2092       if len(padding) != 2:
2093         raise ValueError('`padding` should have two elements. '
2094                          'Found: ' + str(padding))
2095       height_padding = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(padding[0], 2,
2096                                                   '1st entry of padding')
2097       width_padding = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(padding[1], 2,
2098                                                  '2nd entry of padding')
2099       self.padding = (height_padding, width_padding)
2100     else:
2101       raise ValueError('`padding` should be either an int, '
2102                        'a tuple of 2 ints '
2103                        '(symmetric_height_pad, symmetric_width_pad), '
2104                        'or a tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints '
2105                        '((top_pad, bottom_pad), (left_pad, right_pad)). '
2106                        'Found: ' + str(padding))
2107     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=4)
2108 
2109   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
2110     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
2111     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
2112       if input_shape[2] is not None:
2113         rows = input_shape[2] + self.padding[0][0] + self.padding[0][1]
2114       else:
2115         rows = None
2116       if input_shape[3] is not None:
2117         cols = input_shape[3] + self.padding[1][0] + self.padding[1][1]
2118       else:
2119         cols = None
2120       return tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2121           [input_shape[0], input_shape[1], rows, cols])
2122     elif self.data_format == 'channels_last':
2123       if input_shape[1] is not None:
2124         rows = input_shape[1] + self.padding[0][0] + self.padding[0][1]
2125       else:
2126         rows = None
2127       if input_shape[2] is not None:
2128         cols = input_shape[2] + self.padding[1][0] + self.padding[1][1]
2129       else:
2130         cols = None
2131       return tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2132           [input_shape[0], rows, cols, input_shape[3]])
2133 
2134   def call(self, inputs):
2135     return backend.spatial_2d_padding(
2136         inputs, padding=self.padding, data_format=self.data_format)
2137 
2138   def get_config(self):
2139     config = {'padding': self.padding, 'data_format': self.data_format}
2140     base_config = super(ZeroPadding2D, self).get_config()
2141     return dict(list(base_config.items()) + list(config.items()))

2200       dim1_padding = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(padding[0], 2,
2201                                                 '1st entry of padding')
2202       dim2_padding = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(padding[1], 2,
2203                                                 '2nd entry of padding')
2204       dim3_padding = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(padding[2], 2,
2205                                                 '3rd entry of padding')
2206       self.padding = (dim1_padding, dim2_padding, dim3_padding)
2207     else:
2208       raise ValueError(
2209           '`padding` should be either an int, '
2210           'a tuple of 3 ints '
2211           '(symmetric_dim1_pad, symmetric_dim2_pad, symmetric_dim3_pad), '
2212           'or a tuple of 3 tuples of 2 ints '
2213           '((left_dim1_pad, right_dim1_pad),'
2214           ' (left_dim2_pad, right_dim2_pad),'
2215           ' (left_dim3_pad, right_dim2_pad)). '
2216           'Found: ' + str(padding))
2217     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=5)
2218 
2219   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
2220     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
2221     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
2222       if input_shape[2] is not None:
2223         dim1 = input_shape[2] + 2 * self.padding[0][0]
2224       else:
2225         dim1 = None
2226       if input_shape[3] is not None:
2227         dim2 = input_shape[3] + 2 * self.padding[1][0]
2228       else:
2229         dim2 = None
2230       if input_shape[4] is not None:
2231         dim3 = input_shape[4] + 2 * self.padding[2][0]
2232       else:
2233         dim3 = None
2234       return tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2235           [input_shape[0], input_shape[1], dim1, dim2, dim3])
2236     elif self.data_format == 'channels_last':
2237       if input_shape[1] is not None:
2238         dim1 = input_shape[1] + 2 * self.padding[0][1]
2239       else:
2240         dim1 = None
2241       if input_shape[2] is not None:
2242         dim2 = input_shape[2] + 2 * self.padding[1][1]
2243       else:
2244         dim2 = None
2245       if input_shape[3] is not None:
2246         dim3 = input_shape[3] + 2 * self.padding[2][1]
2247       else:
2248         dim3 = None
2249       return tensor_shape.TensorShape(
2250           [input_shape[0], dim1, dim2, dim3, input_shape[4]])
2251 
2252   def call(self, inputs):
2253     return backend.spatial_3d_padding(
2254         inputs, padding=self.padding, data_format=self.data_format)
2255 
2256   def get_config(self):
2257     config = {'padding': self.padding, 'data_format': self.data_format}
2258     base_config = super(ZeroPadding3D, self).get_config()
2259     return dict(list(base_config.items()) + list(config.items()))
