2262 @tf_export('keras.layers.Cropping1D')
2263 class Cropping1D(Layer):
2264   """Cropping layer for 1D input (e.g. temporal sequence).
2265 
2266   It crops along the time dimension (axis 1).
2267 
2268   Arguments:
2269       cropping: int or tuple of int (length 2)
2270           How many units should be trimmed off at the beginning and end of
2271           the cropping dimension (axis 1).
2272           If a single int is provided,
2273           the same value will be used for both.
2274 
2275   Input shape:
2276       3D tensor with shape `(batch, axis_to_crop, features)`
2277 
2278   Output shape:
2279       3D tensor with shape `(batch, cropped_axis, features)`
2280   """
2281 
2282   def __init__(self, cropping=(1, 1), **kwargs):
2283     super(Cropping1D, self).__init__(**kwargs)
2284     self.cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping, 2, 'cropping')
2285     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=3)
2286 
2287   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
2288     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
2289     if input_shape[1] is not None:
2290       length = input_shape[1] - self.cropping[0] - self.cropping[1]
2291     else:
2292       length = None
2293     return tensor_shape.TensorShape([input_shape[0], length, input_shape[2]])
2294 
2295   def call(self, inputs):
2296     if self.cropping[1] == 0:
2297       return inputs[:, self.cropping[0]:, :]
2298     else:
2299       return inputs[:, self.cropping[0]:-self.cropping[1], :]
2300 
2301   def get_config(self):
2302     config = {'cropping': self.cropping}
2303     base_config = super(Cropping1D, self).get_config()

2307 @tf_export('keras.layers.Cropping2D')
2308 class Cropping2D(Layer):
2309   """Cropping layer for 2D input (e.g. picture).
2310 
2311   It crops along spatial dimensions, i.e. height and width.
2312 
2313   Arguments:
2314       cropping: int, or tuple of 2 ints, or tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints.
2315           - If int: the same symmetric cropping
2316               is applied to height and width.
2317           - If tuple of 2 ints:
2318               interpreted as two different
2319               symmetric cropping values for height and width:
2320               `(symmetric_height_crop, symmetric_width_crop)`.
2321           - If tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints:
2322               interpreted as
2323               `((top_crop, bottom_crop), (left_crop, right_crop))`
2324       data_format: A string,
2325           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
2326           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
2327           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
2328           `(batch, height, width, channels)` while `channels_first`
2329           corresponds to inputs with shape
2330           `(batch, channels, height, width)`.
2331           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your
2332           Keras config file at `~/.keras/keras.json`.
2333           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".
2334 
2335   Input shape:
2336       4D tensor with shape:
2337       - If `data_format` is `"channels_last"`:
2338           `(batch, rows, cols, channels)`
2339       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2340           `(batch, channels, rows, cols)`
2341 
2342   Output shape:
2343       4D tensor with shape:
2344       - If `data_format` is `"channels_last"`:
2345           `(batch, cropped_rows, cropped_cols, channels)`
2346       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2347           `(batch, channels, cropped_rows, cropped_cols)`
2348 
2349   Examples:
2350 
2351   ```python
2352       # Crop the input 2D images or feature maps
2353       model = Sequential()
2354       model.add(Cropping2D(cropping=((2, 2), (4, 4)),
2355                            input_shape=(28, 28, 3)))
2356       # now model.output_shape == (None, 24, 20, 3)
2357       model.add(Conv2D(64, (3, 3), padding='same))
2358       model.add(Cropping2D(cropping=((2, 2), (2, 2))))
2359       # now model.output_shape == (None, 20, 16. 64)
2360   ```
2361   """
2362 
2363   def __init__(self, cropping=((0, 0), (0, 0)), data_format=None, **kwargs):
2364     super(Cropping2D, self).__init__(**kwargs)
2365     self.data_format = conv_utils.normalize_data_format(data_format)
2366     if isinstance(cropping, int):
2367       self.cropping = ((cropping, cropping), (cropping, cropping))
2368     elif hasattr(cropping, '__len__'):
2369       if len(cropping) != 2:
2370         raise ValueError('`cropping` should have two elements. '
2371                          'Found: ' + str(cropping))
2372       height_cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping[0], 2,
2373                                                    '1st entry of cropping')
2374       width_cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping[1], 2,
2375                                                   '2nd entry of cropping')
2376       self.cropping = (height_cropping, width_cropping)
2377     else:
2378       raise ValueError('`cropping` should be either an int, '
2379                        'a tuple of 2 ints '
2380                        '(symmetric_height_crop, symmetric_width_crop), '
2381                        'or a tuple of 2 tuples of 2 ints '
2382                        '((top_crop, bottom_crop), (left_crop, right_crop)). '
2383                        'Found: ' + str(cropping))
2384     self.input_spec = InputSpec(ndim=4)
2385 
2386   def compute_output_shape(self, input_shape):
2387     input_shape = tensor_shape.TensorShape(input_shape).as_list()
2388     # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2389     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
2390       return tensor_shape.TensorShape([
2391           input_shape[0], input_shape[1],
2392           input_shape[2] - self.cropping[0][0] - self.cropping[0][1]
2393           if input_shape[2] else None,
2394           input_shape[3] - self.cropping[1][0] - self.cropping[1][1]
2395           if input_shape[3] else None
2396       ])
2397     else:
2398       return tensor_shape.TensorShape([
2399           input_shape[0],
2400           input_shape[1] - self.cropping[0][0] - self.cropping[0][1]
2401           if input_shape[1] else None,
2402           input_shape[2] - self.cropping[1][0] - self.cropping[1][1]
2403           if input_shape[2] else None, input_shape[3]
2404       ])
2405     # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2406 
2407   def call(self, inputs):
2408     # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2409     if self.data_format == 'channels_first':
2410       if self.cropping[0][1] == self.cropping[1][1] == 0:
2411         return inputs[:, :, self.cropping[0][0]:, self.cropping[1][0]:]
2412       elif self.cropping[0][1] == 0:
2413         return inputs[:, :, self.cropping[0][0]:, self.cropping[1][0]:
2414                       -self.cropping[1][1]]
2415       elif self.cropping[1][1] == 0:
2416         return inputs[:, :, self.cropping[0][0]:-self.cropping[0][1],
2417                       self.cropping[1][0]:]
2418       return inputs[:, :, self.cropping[0][0]:-self.cropping[0][1],
2419                     self.cropping[1][0]:-self.cropping[1][1]]
2420     else:
2421       if self.cropping[0][1] == self.cropping[1][1] == 0:
2422         return inputs[:, self.cropping[0][0]:, self.cropping[1][0]:, :]
2423       elif self.cropping[0][1] == 0:
2424         return inputs[:, self.cropping[0][0]:, self.cropping[1][0]:
2425                       -self.cropping[1][1], :]
2426       elif self.cropping[1][1] == 0:
2427         return inputs[:, self.cropping[0][0]:-self.cropping[0][1],
2428                       self.cropping[1][0]:, :]
2429       return inputs[:, self.cropping[0][0]:-self.cropping[0][1], self.cropping[
2430           1][0]:-self.cropping[1][1], :]  # pylint: disable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2431     # pylint: enable=invalid-unary-operand-type
2432 
2433   def get_config(self):
2434     config = {'cropping': self.cropping, 'data_format': self.data_format}
2435     base_config = super(Cropping2D, self).get_config()
2436     return dict(list(base_config.items()) + list(config.items()))

2439 @tf_export('keras.layers.Cropping3D')
2440 class Cropping3D(Layer):
2441   """Cropping layer for 3D data (e.g.
2442 
2443   spatial or spatio-temporal).
2444 
2445   Arguments:
2446       cropping: int, or tuple of 23ints, or tuple of 3 tuples of 2 ints.
2447           - If int: the same symmetric cropping
2448               is applied to depth, height, and width.
2449           - If tuple of 3 ints:
2450               interpreted as two different
2451               symmetric cropping values for depth, height, and width:
2452               `(symmetric_dim1_crop, symmetric_dim2_crop, symmetric_dim3_crop)`.
2453           - If tuple of 3 tuples of 2 ints:
2454               interpreted as
2455               `((left_dim1_crop, right_dim1_crop), (left_dim2_crop,
2456                 right_dim2_crop), (left_dim3_crop, right_dim3_crop))`

2458           one of `channels_last` (default) or `channels_first`.
2459           The ordering of the dimensions in the inputs.
2460           `channels_last` corresponds to inputs with shape
2461           `(batch, spatial_dim1, spatial_dim2, spatial_dim3, channels)`
2462           while `channels_first` corresponds to inputs with shape
2463           `(batch, channels, spatial_dim1, spatial_dim2, spatial_dim3)`.
2464           It defaults to the `image_data_format` value found in your

2466           If you never set it, then it will be "channels_last".

2469       5D tensor with shape:

2471           `(batch, first_axis_to_crop, second_axis_to_crop, third_axis_to_crop,

2473       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2474           `(batch, depth, first_axis_to_crop, second_axis_to_crop,
2475             third_axis_to_crop)`
2476 
2477   Output shape:
2478       5D tensor with shape:
2479       - If `data_format` is `"channels_last"`:
2480           `(batch, first_cropped_axis, second_cropped_axis, third_cropped_axis,
2481             depth)`
2482       - If `data_format` is `"channels_first"`:
2483           `(batch, depth, first_cropped_axis, second_cropped_axis,
2484             third_cropped_axis)`

2488                cropping=((1, 1), (1, 1), (1, 1)),

2499                          'Found: ' + str(cropping))
2500       dim1_cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping[0], 2,
2501                                                  '1st entry of cropping')
2502       dim2_cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping[1], 2,
2503                                                  '2nd entry of cropping')
2504       dim3_cropping = conv_utils.normalize_tuple(cropping[2], 2,
2505                                                  '3rd entry of cropping')
